>> title: Greek Chicken and Potatoes
>> servings: 4
>> prep time: 20 minutes
>> cook time: 50 minutes

1. Preheat oven to 425°F (220°C).

2. In a large bowl, whisk together @extra virgin olive oil{0.25%cup}, lemon juice, minced @garlic{3%cloves}, @oregano{2%tsp}, @salt{1%tsp}, and @black pepper{0.5%tsp}.

3. Add @chicken thighs{2%lbs} to the bowl and coat thoroughly with the marinade. Let sit for 15 minutes.

4. Place @baby potatoes{2%lbs} and @red onion{1} slices in a large roasting pan. Drizzle with some of the marinade from the chicken.

5. Arrange @chicken thighs{2%lbs} on top of the @baby potatoes{2%lbs}, skin side up. Pour any remaining marinade and the @chicken broth{0.5%cup} into the pan.

6. Roast for 45-50 minutes until chicken is golden and @baby potatoes{2%lbs} are tender.

7. Let rest 5 minutes before serving. Serve with simple Greek salad on the side.

-- Category: Mediterranean
-- Cholesterol-friendly benefits: Uses olive oil instead of butter, lean protein, and herbs instead of salt for flavor. The lemon helps with iron absorption from any leafy greens served alongside.
